{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"636f2f02-dc02-4ce4-85b8-56ad280c4035","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. MSTest v3 **dropped support** for two of your three target frameworks:\n\n| Target | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped (EOL) |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped (EOL) |\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for the .NET (Core) side. You'd need to update those targets — e.g., `net5.0` → `net6.0` (or `net8.0`) and `netcoreapp3.1` → `net6.0`.\n\nAdditionally, MSTest v3 consolidates the two packages (`MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter`) into a single **`MSTest`** package, so you'd simplify your `<ItemGroup>` as well.\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for MSTest v3?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"37c585b0-9f7c-4d24-8c5c-69d90bfaa24d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Let me think about what I know:\n\nMSTest v3 (MSTest 3.x) has several breaking changes:\n1. **Minimum supported frameworks**: MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+ and .NET Framework 4.6.2+. It dropped support for:\n   - `netcoreapp3.1` (end of life)\n   - `net5.0` (end of life)\n   \n2. The separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages are replaced by the single `MSTest` meta-package (though the individual packages still exist).\n   \nSo looking at the project's target frameworks: `net462` will work fine since it meets the minimum requirement, but both `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` are incompatible with MSTest v3 and would need to be upgraded to at least `net6.0`.","outputTokens":538,"requestId":"67CD:2636C7:318C777:36BD64D:69FD50C7"},"id":"5df1cede-755d-403a-be8e-c798bc0519ca","timestamp":"2026-05-08T02:56:17.800Z","parentId":"639ff1a4-e512-41b2-80a1-5016d9e7243e"}
